    "instruction": "Load metric.csv and trace.csv. For metric.csv, aggregate by (cmdb_id, kpi_name) and compute: count of points, minimum timestamp, maximum timestamp, mean(value), median(value), and global P95(value). Return at most top 20 rows sorted by count desc, with columns: cmdb_id, kpi_name, count, min_timestamp, max_timestamp, mean_value, median_value, p95_value. For trace.csv, aggregate by trace_name and compute: count of points, min timestamp, max timestamp, mean(value), median(value), and P95(value). Return all trace_name rows (or top 20 by count if many) with columns: trace_name, count, min_timestamp, max_timestamp, mean_value, median_value, p95_value. Keep the outputs compact and do not print full raw time series." 
